said.

Murphy took time last week to talk with
Pitt oﬂicials about where the University
stands on the list.

Pitt spokesman Ken Service said
Murphy and Chancellor Mark Nordenberg
held a meeting about “a variety of issues on
how the city and the University can inter-
act.” Service said nothing official has come
from those talks yet.

The mayor’s final decision may come
very soon, according to Peg McCormick,
Murphy’s spokeswoman.

“I think we’ll have everything tied
down pretty soon,” said McCormick.

          

